                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-340" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY CLARK</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in Butcher-half-lane—rather before eight o'clock, in the evening of the 4th of May, Mr. Cook gave me information—I felt my pocket, and my handkerchief was gone—he directed my attention to the prisoner, who was close to me, and said he had my handkerchief—we charged him with it, and drew it from his trowsers—this is it.</p>
